doctype html
html(lang='en')
  head
    title= title
    link(rel='stylesheet' href='/css/bootstrap.min.css')
  body
    div(class='container')
      h1(class='header')= message
      blockquote User stories:
        ul 1) I can pass a string as a parameter, and it will check to see whether that string contains either a unix timestamp or a natural language date (example: "January 1, 2016", "tomorrow", "12-5-2016", "30 Jun 1981")
        ul 2) If it does, it returns both the Unix timestamp and the natural language form of that date.
        ul 3) If it does not contain a date or Unix timestamp, it returns null for those properties.
      h3 Example usage:
      code https://timestamp-tgallin.herokuapp.com/December%2015,%202015
      br
      code https://timestamp-tgallin.herokuapp.com/1450137600
      br
      code https://timestamp-tgallin.herokuapp.com/today
      br
      code https://timestamp-tgallin.herokuapp.com/a year ago
      h3 Example output:
      code
        | {
        |   "unix": 1450137600,
        |   "natural": "December 15, 2015"
        | }